    protocol: "IMMEDIATE PLACEMENT + GUIDED:\nPer Cosyn 2023 EAO: guided surgery preferred over freehand for immediate placement.\n\nACCURACY HIERARCHY (Wu 2025 NMA):\n1) Combined static+dynamic ranked best\n2) Robotic (rCAIS) — highest apex accuracy\n3) Fully guided static — best coronal control\n4) Dynamic navigation — best angular control\n5) Freehand — significantly inferior to ALL guided", evidence: "GUIDED VS FREEHAND: THE EVIDENCE\n\nPer Varga 2020 LANDMARK RCT: freehand 7.03° vs fully guided 3.04°. Per Khaohoen 2025 MA: guided 3.87° less angular deviation than freehand.\nPer Alshadidi 2026 RCT: fully guided 45 min / 5% complications vs freehand 75 min / 20% complications.\nPer Reiff 2026 MA: both static and dynamic significantly better than freehand; no sig. difference between static and dynamic.\n\nGUIDE TYPES (by accuracy):\n1) Tooth-supported: MOST accurate (shortest distance to bone, rigid fixation)\n2) Mucosa-supported: intermediate (compressible tissue reduces accuracy)\n3) Bone-supported: requires flap, pins for fixation\n\nSLEEVE-TO-BONE DISTANCE:\nPer Guentsch 2021: 2mm sleeve-bone distance = 0.22mm 3D deviation. Accuracy decreases with distance.\nPer Hang 2025: sleeveless guides showed BETTER accuracy (1.65° vs 2.41°, p=0.0001) — counterintuitive but validated.\n\nFULL-ARCH GUIDED (Stackable Guides):\nPer Bjelica 2026: stackable templates — 1.25° angular, 0.96mm neck deviation. All below safety thresholds.\nSequence: pin fixation guide → bone reduction guide → implant guide → provisional guide.\n\nFLAPLESS GUIDED:\nPer Romandini 2023 MA: -3.88° angular, -0.75mm apical deviation, 24 min shorter surgery, less pain.\n⚠ 12% intraoperative complication rate with flapless; 7% inability to complete protocol.\n\nPer Nicchio 2023: fully guided 1.52mm vs partially guided 2.25mm apical deviation (sig.).\nSTATIC vs DYNAMIC: Per Pellegrino 2021 MA: dynamic entry 0.81mm, apex 0.91mm, angular 3.81°. No sig. diff vs static. Choose based on ecosystem and case.\n\nSOFTWARE: Per Singthong 2024 RCT: coDiagnostiX vs Implant Studio — no sig. diff; both acceptable for inexperienced operators. Both showed shallower-than-planned depth (0.71–0.84mm). Main platforms: coDiagnostiX (Straumann), Implant Studio (3Shape), BlueSkyPlan (open), R2Gate.\n\n⚠ SAFETY MARGIN: maintain ≥2mm from planned position to vital structures (Tahmaseb 2018 MA).", notes: "GUIDED VS FREEHAND: THE EVIDENCE\n\nPer Varga 2020 LANDMARK RCT: freehand 7.03° vs fully guided 3.04°. Per Khaohoen 2025 MA: guided 3.87° less angular deviation than freehand.\nPer Alshadidi 2026 RCT: fully guided 45 min / 5% complications vs freehand 75 min / 20% complications.\nPer Reiff 2026 MA: both static and dynamic significantly better than freehand; no sig. difference between static and dynamic.\n\nGUIDE TYPES (by accuracy):\n1) Tooth-supported: MOST accurate (shortest distance to bone, rigid fixation)\n2) Mucosa-supported: intermediate (compressible tissue reduces accuracy)\n3) Bone-supported: requires flap, pins for fixation\n\nSLEEVE-TO-BONE DISTANCE:\nPer Guentsch 2021: 2mm sleeve-bone distance = 0.22mm 3D deviation. Accuracy decreases with distance.\nPer Hang 2025: sleeveless guides showed BETTER accuracy (1.65° vs 2.41°, p=0.0001) — counterintuitive but validated.\n\nFULL-ARCH GUIDED (Stackable Guides):\nPer Bjelica 2026: stackable templates — 1.25° angular, 0.96mm neck deviation. All below safety thresholds.\nSequence: pin fixation guide → bone reduction guide → implant guide → provisional guide.\n\nFLAPLESS GUIDED:\nPer Romandini 2023 MA: -3.88° angular, -0.75mm apical deviation, 24 min shorter surgery, less pain.\n⚠ 12% intraoperative complication rate with flapless; 7% inability to complete protocol.\n\nIMMEDIATE PLACEMENT + GUIDED:\nPer Nicchio 2023: fully guided 1.52mm vs partially guided 2.25mm apical deviation (sig.).\nPer Cosyn 2023 EAO: guided surgery preferred over freehand for immediate placement.\n\nACCURACY HIERARCHY (Wu 2025 NMA):\n1) Combined static+dynamic ranked best\n2) Robotic (rCAIS) — highest apex accuracy\n3) Fully guided static — best coronal control\n4) Dynamic navigation — best angular control\n5) Freehand — significantly inferior to ALL guided\n\nSTATIC vs DYNAMIC: Per Pellegrino 2021 MA: dynamic entry 0.81mm, apex 0.91mm, angular 3.81°. No sig. diff vs static. Choose based on ecosystem and case.\n\nSOFTWARE: Per Singthong 2024 RCT: coDiagnostiX vs Implant Studio — no sig. diff; both acceptable for inexperienced operators. Both showed shallower-than-planned depth (0.71–0.84mm). Main platforms: coDiagnostiX (Straumann), Implant Studio (3Shape), BlueSkyPlan (open), R2Gate.\n\n⚠ SAFETY MARGIN: maintain ≥2mm from planned position to vital structures (Tahmaseb 2018 MA).",
    refs: ["varga-2020-guided-rct","alshadidi-2026-guided-rct","reiff-2026-static-dynamic","wu-2025-robotic-nma","markiewicz-2025-guide-types","khaohoen-2025-guided-ma","guentsch-2021-sleeve-distance","hang-2025-sleeveless","bjelica-2026-stackable","romandini-2023-flapless-ma","pellegrino-2021-dynamic-ma","singthong-2024-software-rct","nicchio-2023-guided-immediate","cosyn-2023-eao-iip"]
