    id: "immediate-placement-protocol", name: "Immediate Implant Placement Protocol", cat: "Protocol — Immediate Placement",
    design: "7) If immediate provisionalization: insertion torque ≥35 N·cm, ISQ >65\n8) Connective tissue graft from tuberosity for soft tissue stability (recommended in esthetic zone)", protocol: "IMMEDIATE IMPLANT PLACEMENT (IIP): EVIDENCE-BASED PROTOCOL\n\n• Intact alveolus → immediate placement with immediate provisionalization is REFERENCE CHOICE\n• Bone-to-implant gap >2mm should be sought and grafted\n• Compromised alveolus → staged approach preferred\n\n• Intact socket + adequate bone → immediate placement\n• Compromised socket → early (6–8 wk) or delayed (>6 mo) with augmentation\n\nPREREQUISITES (EAO):\n1) No acute infection\n2) Apical and palatal/lingual bone for anchorage\n3) Tooth within bone envelope\n4) Favorable socket morphology\n5) No midfacial recession\n6) Appropriate implant selection\n7) Experienced surgeon\n\nGUIDED vs FREEHAND FOR IIP:\nCBCT is REQUIRED for immediate placement planning.\n\nPROTOCOL STEPS:\n1) Atraumatic extraction (periotome, physics forceps — preserve buccal plate)\n2) Thorough socket debridement\n3) Palatal/lingual positioning (NOT centered in socket)\n4) Guided osteotomy if using surgical guide\n5) Implant placement — engage ≥3mm apical bone beyond socket\n6) Assess gap: if >2mm horizontal gap → graft with slow-resorbing xenograft (Bio-Oss)\nLOADING DECISION:\n• Posterior: delayed loading safer (Per Ko 2021: immediate 69.4% vs delayed 100%)\n• ⚠ Risk factors for immediate loading failure: diabetes, periodontitis, smoking, inadequate primary stability", evidence: "Per Cosyn 2023 EAO Position Paper:\nPer Cardaropoli 2025 Consensus:\nPer Nicchio 2023: fully guided 1.52mm vs partially guided 2.25mm apical deviation — fully guided significantly better.\n• Esthetic zone single tooth: immediate provisionalization acceptable with adequate stability (Per Wittneben 2023: 99.2% 1-yr survival)", notes: "IMMEDIATE IMPLANT PLACEMENT (IIP): EVIDENCE-BASED PROTOCOL\n\nPer Cosyn 2023 EAO Position Paper:\n• Intact alveolus → immediate placement with immediate provisionalization is REFERENCE CHOICE\n• Bone-to-implant gap >2mm should be sought and grafted\n• Compromised alveolus → staged approach preferred\n\nPer Cardaropoli 2025 Consensus:\n• Intact socket + adequate bone → immediate placement\n• Compromised socket → early (6–8 wk) or delayed (>6 mo) with augmentation\n\nPREREQUISITES (EAO):\n1) No acute infection\n2) Apical and palatal/lingual bone for anchorage\n3) Tooth within bone envelope\n4) Favorable socket morphology\n5) No midfacial recession\n6) Appropriate implant selection\n7) Experienced surgeon\n\nGUIDED vs FREEHAND FOR IIP:\nPer Nicchio 2023: fully guided 1.52mm vs partially guided 2.25mm apical deviation — fully guided significantly better.\nCBCT is REQUIRED for immediate placement planning.\n\nPROTOCOL STEPS:\n1) Atraumatic extraction (periotome, physics forceps — preserve buccal plate)\n2) Thorough socket debridement\n3) Palatal/lingual positioning (NOT centered in socket)\n4) Guided osteotomy if using surgical guide\n5) Implant placement — engage ≥3mm apical bone beyond socket\n6) Assess gap: if >2mm horizontal gap → graft with slow-resorbing xenograft (Bio-Oss)\n7) If immediate provisionalization: insertion torque ≥35 N·cm, ISQ >65\n8) Connective tissue graft from tuberosity for soft tissue stability (recommended in esthetic zone)\n\nLOADING DECISION:\n• Esthetic zone single tooth: immediate provisionalization acceptable with adequate stability (Per Wittneben 2023: 99.2% 1-yr survival)\n• Posterior: delayed loading safer (Per Ko 2021: immediate 69.4% vs delayed 100%)\n• ⚠ Risk factors for immediate loading failure: diabetes, periodontitis, smoking, inadequate primary stability",
